# Epic 4: Logistic Regression

## Introduction

Logistic Regression is a supervised machine learning algorithm used for classification problems. In the OptiCrop Smart Agricultural Production Optimization System, Logistic Regression is applied to predict the most suitable crop based on soil nutrients and environmental conditions.

## Dataset

The model uses the agricultural dataset containing the following features:

* Nitrogen (N)
* Phosphorous (P)
* Potassium (K)
* Temperature
* Humidity
* pH
* Rainfall

The crop label serves as the target variable.

## Data Preparation

Before training the model, the crop labels were converted into numerical values using Label Encoding. The dataset was then divided into training and testing sets using an 80:20 ratio.

## Model Training

The Logistic Regression model was trained using the training dataset. During training, the algorithm learned the relationship between the input features and the crop labels.

## Model Evaluation

The trained model was evaluated using the testing dataset. Performance was measured using accuracy, a classification report, and a confusion matrix.

## Results

The Logistic Regression model successfully classified crops based on soil and environmental parameters. The evaluation metrics demonstrated that the model is capable of making accurate crop recommendations.

## Conclusion

Logistic Regression provided an effective baseline classification model for the OptiCrop system. The trained model can be used for predicting suitable crops and forms the foundation for deployment in the application.
